data.title: Victoria's Secret Angel Lais Ribeiro, 33, reveals the ULTIMATE beauty and wellness hacks behind her supermodel looks - and the 'top secret' Brazilian treatment she swears by to stay in such amazing sh
data.meta_description: In an exclusive chat with FEMAIL, Brazilian model Lais Ribeiro, 33, revealed all of the beauty, wellness, workout and mindfulness practices that she swears by behind-the-scenes. Read about it here.
data.text:
While stunning supermodel Lais Ribeiro may look effortlessly gorgeous as she's gracing the covers of magazines or storming the runway, it takes a lot of self-care to get both the body and mind of a Victoria's Secret Angel right.

In an exclusive chat with FEMAIL, Ribeiro, 33, revealed all of the beauty, wellness, workout and mindfulness practices that she swears by behind-the-scenes.

Ribeiro, from Miguel Alves, State of Piau, Brazil, got her start in the modeling world in 2009. Since her career took off, she's worked with designers like Givenchy, Dolce & Gabbana, and Ralph Lauren.

She became a Victoria's Secret Angel in 2015, and was the fourth Black model to wear the Victoria's Secret Fantasy Bra since the fashion show got its start in 1995.

Now, Ribeiro has lifted the lid on her ultimate beauty and wellness secrets, and FEMAIL has broken them all down for you.

Getting steamy: Combining a sauna with a cold plunge is one of her go-tos

One of Ribeiro's favorite things to help her body recover from her workouts is the combination of an at-home sauna session followed by a cold plunge.

The practice can provide many benefits, according to National Geographic, including 'improved mood' and muscle recovery after a strenuous workout.

'I work out three times a week,' she divulged to DailyMail.com. 'I try to do an ice/sauna those times because it will help me with the soreness.'

'I sleep so much better,' she added. 'The combination is great for circulation as well.'

But it wasn't easy to get used to the shocking temperatures of the cold plunge at first, she admitted.

'Because my husband is an athlete, he's always pushing me to do some kind of crazy stuff,' she said of her partner, former NBA player Joakim Noah.

'I hated [the ice] at first and then I started to get used to it.

'The ice is a love/hate relationship.'

Lymphatic drainage massages are her 'top secret' technique

'As a good Brazilian, I love a lymphatic,' Ribeiro told DailyMail.com. 'Everywhere I go, I really try to find someone that does an amazing drainage.'

However, she called Los Angeles-based masseuse Flavia Lanini, who she has known for more than 10 years, the 'best of them all.'

'I have never found someone like her before,' Ribeiro confessed. 'I'm not lying, her hands are pretty amazing.'

Lymphatic drainage massages differ from standard massages as they specifically target areas of the body to reduce swelling and inflammation.

This massage will manually move the fluid in your body into its healthy lymph nodes.

The Ocean Drive Magazine February cover star furthered that the massages created a difference in her body that was noticeable immediately.

'Lymphatic drainage is my top secret for sure,' she added.

To combat any puffiness on the face, the Victoria's Secret Angel said that she liked to use an ice roller, especially when she was working.

'It takes off the puffiness of your eyes and gives you a little sculpture in your eye as well,' she said.

Working out is a top priority, even when the model is on-the-go

Ribeiro seems to have figured out a balanced workout routine, whether she's traveling or at home.

When she's not on-the-go, Ribeiro likes to work out with a trainer and lift weights.

She'll also mix in some yoga, something she says that she 'fell in love with.'

'I incorporate yoga because it's half stretching and half grounding,' the supermodel told DailyMail.com.

'It's really good for my mental health and I'm ready to attack the day, calm and relaxed,' she continued.

But while she's traveling, the Sports Illustrated Swimsuit model likes to stay in the groove by working out with the SotoMethod, a workout that's a unique mix of cardio and sculpting movements founded by Hilary Hoffman.

The guided classes are available virtually, which Ribeiro utilizes while she's not able to work out at home.

'It's so hard,' the supermodel raved about the full-body workout. 'So I'm in love because it's easy when I'm traveling, when I don't have a trainer.'

Small swaps have helped the model immensely in her beauty and wellness routines

Over the years, making small swaps and changes where it's possible have really helped the model level up both her beauty and wellness routines.

Recently, she traded her pillowcase for one made of silk, something she credits for helping save her from hair loss.

'My hair, I don't know why, it was just like falling apart,' she told DailyMail.com.

'I had to do something about it,' she continued, adding that she had changed up her diet as well to combat the symptoms. 'My hair stopped falling [out] but I think the silk pillowcase helped me with that as well.'

She has also slowly incorporated green juice, swapping coffee out instead, into her daily routine - although she didn't always love it.

'It's funny because my entire family, they love coffee,' Ribeiro told DailyMail.com.

'I just don't like the way it makes me feel because my heart is beating really fast.'

She started digging in to her greens about a year ago, she said, and says that drinking AG1, a dietary supplement by Athletic Greens packed with tons of veggies, really helped her get started.

Now, she makes her own from scratch in the morning, alternating it daily with a protein shake full of collagen and creatine.

The model also spoke out about how her routine had changed since she turned 30.

'I think for me at this time of my life, it's more about food and how my body reacts,' Ribeiro told DailyMail.com.

'I had nothing before I was 30, like absolutely nothing. I could eat anything and I didn't need to to work out that much, but now it's like a big effort.

'I'm here on my new journey.'

Her daily routine: Ribeiro's non-negotiables

Upon waking up, there are a few non-negotiables that Ribeiro must do every day.

'I wake up, I take my son to school before anything else,' the Galore magazine cover star shared of her 15-year-old son, Alexandre.

'I always try to make a list of daily goals, which is like take care of my skin, face wash, I put lotion on the serum and the vitamin C.

'I do that every single day in the morning.'

After that, Ribeiro always makes sure that she scrapes her tongue, and then takes her vitamins, like iron, Vitamin D, and magnesium.

Of course, going in her sauna every day is another non-negotiable, she noted to DailyMail.com.

Mental health and mindfulness matter - and it's important to slow down

While Ribeiro balances her busy career with being a devoted mom and wife, she likes to slow down by doing various mindfulness practices.

The model works with a meditation and reiki teacher, who has shared many valuable tips with her, like the importance of avoiding your phone first thing in the morning.

'Sometimes my teacher says when you wake up, take at least 10, 15 minutes sit down without [the phone] and just let the thoughts come and let them go,' she described to DailyMail.com.

'It's really hard, but I try not to look at my phone for at least an hour after I wake up.'

The Alo Yoga partner also tries to meditate when she can, but admitted that it took her some time to get the hang of it.

'It took years for me to at least sit down in silence and not have anything in my mind,' Ribeiro shared.

'We have everything going like a bullet train, thinking about everything at the same time,' she admitted.

Ribeiro stays true to her roots by using and supporting brands from Brazil

Another important part of Ribeiro's routine is using products from NativaSPA, which is a plant-based Brazilian brand that she has been using since she was young.

She says the products really help her dry skin - especially their oils and lotions.

Ribeiro uses the brand's oil and lotion every day, and the scrub a few times a week, which she promises has 'many benefits' for the skin.

When she's in her sauna, the Victoria's Secret superstar often likes to apply the oil to her body with a dry brush, explaining to DailyMail.com that it helps with her circulation.

'It also helps with taking off the dead skin, it's like exfoliation inside of the sauna,' she said.

Growing up, Ribeiro said that her family often turned to organic ingredients when it came to taking care of their skin and hair health.

'The women in my family are funny because the only one who does those things for skincare is my sister, we're two years apart,' Ribeiro said.

She said that she never really saw her grandma, mom or aunts put on make up, joking that they just started getting into it now.

'They've always been very natural, use organic ingredients like coconut oil, aloe vera for the hair, mixing it with the conditioner, things like that,' she said.

'I don't think they had time, they were working, they had kids, it was a different mentality as well.'
